$ vim option: endofline
@ endofline

The value of `endofline` determines, together with the value of `binary` and `fixeol`, if a file's last line will be written with a *EOL* symbol (i.e. CR, LF or CR+LF).

The abbrevated option of `endofline` is `eol`.

sa:
  → development/vim/options/fixendofline,
  → development/vim/options/binary

  → development/line-break
